There are two ways to login into stackstorm:
===========================================
   WebUI 
   Command Line Interface(CLI)
WebUI - http://hostname:80/
CLI:  st2 login <user_name> -p <password>
    Note: This login is valid for 24hrs.  

How to Change Password for StackStorm ?
   Run: sudo htpasswd /etc/st2/htpasswd st2admin

We have two types of CLIs on StackStorm Server.
----------------------------------------------
st2ctl       -->  To work with StackStorm for Administartion/Configruation. (To get help: st2ctl --help)
st2 	     -->  To Execute Automation Tasks.(To get help: st2 --help)


Important paths:
================
 /opt/stackstorm
 /etc/st2
 /var/log/st2 
Python Version is used by StackStorm:
    st2 --version 
    /opt/stackstorm/st2/bin/python3 --version


Note: One-line/Quick Install process will automatically start stackstorm even if we reboot system.
